System Description 
The objective of this lab was to design and implement a frequency detection circuit that activates an LED only when a 17 kHz signal is present. The circuit consists of three main functional blocks:
•	A band-pass filter centered at 17 kHz to isolate the desired frequency.
•	A peak detector to convert the AC signal into a DC level proportional to the signal amplitude.
•	A comparator (LM339) to compare the detected DC voltage against a reference voltage and drive an LED indicator when the target frequency is detected.
The design was first simulated in LTspice, then implemented on a breadboard and tested using a Keysight DSOX1202G oscilloscope with Frequency Response Analysis (FRA).

LTspice final Circuit 

 
The band-pass filter was implemented using two cascaded active filter stages, each built with an operational amplifier. Each stage functions as a second-order band-pass filter, resulting in an overall fourth-order filter.

